rticularly land rights. He shows that literary views of natives, both positive and negative, emphasize the same charac-teristics and he suggests that escape from this limited vision may open the door to solving the problems of native sovereignty.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Canadian.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356194640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773561946423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773561946/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles